## âœ¨ Features

VitalsWidget moves system monitoring from the top panel directly onto your desktop, inspired by modern, minimal UI design.

* **Real-time Monitoring**: High-precision tracking for CPU, RAM, Storage, Temperature, and GPU.
* **Elegant Ring Design**: Circular progress rings with centered SVG icons that adapt to your theme.
* **Floating Workspace**: Position the widget anywhere on your screen using precise percentage-based coordinates.
* **Deep Customization**:
    * **Colors**: Individual ring colors, background, and borders.
    * **Layout**: Adjustable circle diameter, ring thickness, and spacing.
    * **Visibility**: Toggle labels and icons to match your aesthetic.
* **GPU Support**: Native support for both NVIDIA (`nvidia-smi`) and AMD (`radeontop`).

---

## ðŸ›  Installation

### Prerequisites
| Requirement | Version |
| :--- | :--- |
| **GNOME Shell** | 45, 46, 47, 48, or 49 |
| **Node.js** | 18+ |
| **TypeScript** | 5.3+ |

### From Source
```bash
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone [https://github.com/ctrln3rd/vitals-widget.git](https://github.com/ctrln3rd/vitals-widget.git)
cd vitals-widget

# 2. Install dev dependencies
npm install

# 3. Build and install to local extensions folder
make install

# 4. Enable the extension
gnome-extensions enable vitalswidget@ctrln3rd.github.com